<HEADLINE> Schedule for Tour of South China Sea Cycle Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Following are the schedule
for the week-long, 601.1-kilomter Tour of South China Sea Cycle
Race '98 starting in Hong Kong on Saturday:
</P>
<P>
Stage 1, Saturday, December 26, 1998, Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR):
</P>
<P>
16 kilometers time trial, Cheung Tung Road, Northern Lantau
Island;
</P>
<P>
Stage 2, Sunday, December 27, 1998, Hong Kong SAR:
</P>
<P>
88 KM criterium, South Apron, Kai Tak Airport;
</P>
<P>
Stage 3, Monday, December 28, 1998, Guangzhou, South China:
</P>
<P>
135.6 KM individual road race, Lake Tianlu;
</P>
<P>
Stage 4, Tuesday, December 29, 1998, Zhuhai, South China:
</P>
<P>
108 KM criterium, Zhuhai International Racing Circuit;
</P>
<P>
Stage 5, Wednesday, December 30, 1998, Zhuhai, South China:
</P>
<P>
97.5 KM criterium, Zhuhai Sports Complex;
</P>
<P>
Stage 6, Thursday, December 31, 1998, Macao:
</P>
<P>
90 KM individual road race, Coloane;
</P>
<P>
Stage 7, Friday, January 1, 1999, Macao:
</P>
<P>
66 KM criterium, Jockey Club Square.
</P>
