<HEADLINE> Allocation of Portfolios in Nepal's New Coalition Govt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Nepali Prime Minister Girija
Prasad Koirala Friday formed an 11-member cabinet comprising the
Nepali Congress (NC), the Communist Party of Nepal (United
Marxism-Leninism, CPN-UML) and the Nepal Sadbhavana Party (NSP).
</P>
<P>
The cabinet includes one member of the Upper House of
Parliament nominated by King Birendra. The following is the
allocation of portfolios in the government:
</P>
<P>
1. Girija Prasad Koirala: prime minister and minister for
foreign and defense affairs, royal palace affairs, agriculture,
labor, supplies, forest and soil conservation, land reform and
management, works and transport and housing and physical planning
(NC)
</P>
<P>
2. Govind Raj Joshi: minister for home affairs and general
administration (NC)
</P>
<P>
3. K.B. Gurung: minister for education and women and social
welfare (NC)
</P>
<P>
4. Purna Bahadur Khadka: minister for youth, sports and culture
and commerce (NC)
</P>
<P>
5. Jaya Prakash Prasad Gupta: minister for information and
communications and parliamentary affairs (NC)
</P>
<P>
6. Bharat Mohan Adhikari: minister for finance and law and
justice (CPN-UML)
</P>
<P>
7. Amrit Kumar Bohara: minister for local development (CPN-UML)
</P>
<P>
8. Pradip Nepal: minister for health and water resources
(CPN-UML)
</P>
<P>
9. Bhim Rawal: minister for tourism and civil aviation and
science and technology (CPN-UML)
</P>
<P>
10. Gajendra Narayan Singh: minister for industry (NSP)
</P>
<P>
11. Ramesh Nath Pandey: minister for environment and population
(nominated by King Birendra) 
</P>
</TEXT>
