<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan President to Visit India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan President
Chandrika Kumaratunga will pay a three-day state visit to India
from Sunday during which the two countries are expected to sign an
agreement on free trade.
</P>
<P>
According to a program issued by Indian Ministry of External
Affairs, the president will called on Indian President Kocheril
Raman Narayanan, Prime Minister Atal Behari Vajpayee and Congress
leader Sonia Gandha to discuss with them the bilateral trade and
political issues.
</P>
<P>
She will also expected to brief the Indian leaders on possible
talks between the Sri Lankan government and the Tamil rebels and
her attempt to secure parliamentary approval for an autonomy
package for the Tamil-dominated northeast.
</P>
<P>
The two countries are set to sign an agreement that will
provide Sri Lankan goods with unlimited access to Indian markets.
</P>
</TEXT>
