<HEADLINE> Concept of 21st Century has Nothing to Do With India: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 25 (Xinhua) -- A Cabinet minister said here
Friday that the talk of stepping into the 21st century was a
western concept and had nothing to do with India.
</P>
<P>
"What have we do with the 21st century?" Human Resource
Development Minister murli Manohar Joshi asked in a lecture during
an gathering here, adding that India's history and tradition was
much older than the intellectual giants in the west could even
think.
</P>
<P>
Ridiculing the hips over the stepping into the 21st century,
the minister said the concept made history marching backward
instead of moving ahead. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
