<HEADLINE> Moslem Groups to Boycott U.S., British Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 25 (Xinhua) -- A coalition of Moslem
organizations in South Africa said Friday that it was organizing
a boycott of selected American and British products to protest
the bombing of Iraq by the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The coalition, known as the Iraq Action Committee, said that
the boycott was to be international and was aimed at developing a
culture of resistance to gross violence and crimes against
humanity as happened in Iraq, the committee said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The coalition called for a "united action of peace-loving
people internationally and within South Africa to condemn the
unilateral bombing and massacre of the Iraqi people by the United
States and Britain."
</P>
<P>
Spokesman for the organization Yusuf Saloojee said a range of
protest actions were being planned throughout South Africa
against the U.S. and Britain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
