<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kyrgyz Parliament Confirms New Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, December 25 (Xinhua) -- The Kyrgyz parliament on Friday
confirmed Zhumabek Ibraimov as the country's new prime minister,
Interfax reported.
</P>
<P>
Ibraimov was nominated by President Askar Akayev following the
dismissal last Wednesday of former prime minister Kubanychbek
Zhumaliyev.
</P>
<P>
Zhumaliyev's cabinet was fired for its poor coordination with
the central bank and the subsequent financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Ibraimov had worked as the director of a car-assembly
enterprise in Bishkek, the head of the Bishkek city
administration, the head of the Kyrgyz Presidential
Administration.
</P>
<P>
