<HEADLINE> Turkish Police Seize 200 Kilograms of Heroin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Turkish police Friday seized
200 kilograms of heroin in an anti-drug operation in northern
Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Acting on a tip-off, the police stopped a truck in Bolu
province, about 200 kilometers from northwestern Ankara and found
the drugs in the truck heading for Istanbul, the largest city of
Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The police detained two suspects involved in the case, said the
agency.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish police have seized over 10 tonnes of drugs including
5.3 tonnes of hashish and 3.8 tonnes of heroin in 2,928 operations
against drug trafficking by December this year.
</P>
<P>
And 5,172 Turkish people and 293 foreigners were detained on
drug smuggling charges, and 15 smugglers were killed in clashes
with the police in the same period.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is on a transit route of drugs from the border areas of
Afghanistan and Pakistan to Europe. 
</P>
