<HEADLINE> Beijing Builds Farm for Mental Patients </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 26 (Xinhua) -- The first phase of a unique
combined medical and farming experiment was launched today to help
rehabilitate many Beijing mental patients.
</P>
<P>
Jin Dacheng, vice-head of the Beijing Municipal Bureau of
Health, explained that there are over 10,000 mental patients in
Beijing, while there are only 6,000 beds for them.
</P>
<P>
It means that lots of patients cannot get sufficient medical
treatment, creating problems for the patients' families as well as
the society.
</P>
<P>
The farm project combines medical and recovery treatment which
encourages patients to help raise fish, geese, chickens, ducks and
goats. According to doctors, getting involved in some farming
activities will not only ease the side effect of medicines, but
also shorten the patients' recovery period.,
</P>
<P>
It allows the society in general to assist the hospital with
the treatment of such patients.
</P>
<P>
Huang Zheng, who is in charge of the farm, announced that the
first phase of the project was complete with a total investment of
2.48 million yuan (300,000 U.S. dollars). And the remaining two
phases are expected to be finished by the end of 1999.
</P>
<P>
The farm is now able to receive 120 patients, and will be
able to accommodate 260 patients when fully operational.
</P>
<P>
The monthly expenditure per patient is just 600 to 900 yuan,
which is comparatively low compared with the usual hospital
expenses of 2,000 to 3,000 yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
