<HEADLINE> Beijing Sets Up New Hi-Tech Industrial Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 26 (Xinhua) -- Qinghua University, China's
leading institution of higher learning, set up a hi-tech
industrial park with Beijing's Miyun County today to explore the
hi-tech potential in the county.
</P>
<P>
Located at about 60 kilometers northeast to the Beijing proper,
the Qinghua (Miyun) Hi-Tech Industrial Park covers an area of 120
hectares with buildings' floor space reaching 500,000 square
meters. It contains industrial bases of information, environmental
protection, new energy, electronics and nuclear technology
application.
</P>
<P>
With the support of Qinghua's talent resources and technology
and the sound investment environment of Miyun, the park is
expected to turn out an annual output value of 1.5 billion yuan
(about 180 million U.S. dollars) in three years. The figure is
expected to exceed 5 billion yuan after the completion of the
industrial park.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Yuanqing, vice-minister of education, said today that the
industrial park will help accelerate the industrial application of
Qinghua's scientific research successes and boost Beijing's
economic growth as a whole. 
