<HEADLINE> Rail, Road Accidents Kill 22 in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 26 (Xinhua) -- Eleven coal miners were
killed and six others injured Friday night when a speeding goods
train plowed into their bus at a manned level-crossing in the
eastern Bihar State.
</P>
<P>
The Press Trust of India (PTI) said the bus carrying the miners
to their night shift tried to pass through the crossing after its
driver took away the keys by force from the gatekeeper who had
already closed the gates for the train to pass.
