<HEADLINE> Security Guard Dies in Lake Rescue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 26 (Xinhua) -- A young security guard on his
way to work died Friday as he and a friend tried to rescue three
fishermen who had fallen through the ice in Beijing's Longtanhu
Park.
</P>
<P>
One of the fishermen who offered to help also perished.
</P>
<P>
The tragedy unfolded at noon when Zhang Lei, 22 years old, and
his colleague Liu Huanwei rushed to help when he heard the cries
of three migrant workers who had been fishing through a hole in
the ice in the middle of the lake.
</P>
<P>
Zhang and Liu quickly untied their belts and tried to pull
the victims out of the freezing water. Suddenly the ice also gave
way under Zhang and he drowned.
</P>
<P>
Two of the victims were rescued by Liu with the help of
passerby Hou Zhonghua, 46.
</P>
<P>
Zhang was employed by the Chongwen Security Branch Company at
the Hongqiao Department Store and was described as a model worker.
</P>
