<HEADLINE> Stockholm Replaces Copenhagen as Tourism Capital in North Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, December 26 (Xinhua) -- Stockholm has taken the
title of tourism capital in North Europe from Copenhagen, capital
of Denmark, with 6.5 million tourist arrivals this year.
</P>
<P>
A total of 6.5 million tourists have visited the Swedish
capital so far this year, 3 million more than those who came to
Copenhagen during the same period, Stockholm city tourism
department said.
</P>
<P>
This is a 10 percent increase from that of 1997, said Goeran
Laangs, a tourism officer of Stockholm.
</P>
<P>
The number of tourists from Italy and Spain rose by 50 percent
and 30 percent respectively. The city also received more tourists
from Japan.
</P>
<P>
Tourism brings not only enormous revenues but also create job
opportunities for the city. Every 10 percent rise in tourist
arrivals will create 2,000 jobs, the officer said.
</P>
<P>
The increase in tourist arrivals was a result of strengthened
promotional work done by the Stockholm tourism department in
recent years in other European countries, the United States and
Japan.
</P>
<P>
It is expected that 20 modern hotels will be built in the
Swedish capital in the next ten years, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
