<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 26 (Xinhua) -- Over 10,000 Somalis have
crossed into Ethiopian territory fleeing the drought that hit
southern Somalia, The Ethiopian Herald reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted Abubaker Abdi, representative of the
Disaster Prevention and Preparedness Bureau of Somali Region as
saying that the Somalis were displaced from the Gerkayu, Zerwery
and Peasnod localities of southern Somalia and are camped in
