<HEADLINE> Rehabilitation Going Smoothly in Northeastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, December 26 (Xinhua) -- More than half of the flood
victims in northeast China's Jilin Province have moved into newly
built housing, and the rest are now properly settled in the chilly
winter.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last month, more than 117,000 rooms had been
built for over 46,000 flood-affected families, accounting for some
50 percent of the total, and more will be built in the
coming spring.
</P>
<P>
Most urban public facilities and installations have also been
restored, and the water supply has returned to normal.
</P>
<P>
Jilin was hit by a deluge this summer that cost 370 million
yuan (45 million U.S. dollars) in direct losses in eight cities
and counties and destroyed 235,000 rooms. More than 85,800
families were left homeless. 
</P>
