<HEADLINE> Construction Work on China's Beilun Power Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, December 26 (Xinhua) -- The second phase of
construction work on the Beilun Power Station in the port city in
Zhejiang Province, which began in June last year, is going
smoothly and one of the three generating units is expected to go
into operation by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
The project, which is expected to cost 12.2 billion yuan (1.47
billion U.S. dollars), will involve installing three coal-fueled
generating units imported from overseas.
