<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0530 GMT, December 26 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Azerbaijan and a consortium of Japanese oil
companies on Friday signed a parity contract to explore and
develop the former Soviet republic's Caspian Sea oil.
</P>
<P>
The deal, on the Yanan-Tava, Ateshgyakh-3 and Muran-Deniz
structures in the southern part of the Azerbaijan sector of the
Caspian Sea, was signed in a ceremony attended by Azeri President
Heydar Aliyev.ported.(Azerbaijan-Japan-oil)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ALMA ATA -- The Uzbek parliament Thursday passed the 1999 draft
budget, which estimates revenues at 548 billion som (5 billion
U.S.dollars) and expenditures of 601 billion som (5.5 billion
dollars), with a budget deficit of 5 3 billion som (500 million
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Uzbekistan President Islam Karimov said in parliament that the
main points of the draft include cutting military and
administrative expenditures and measures to revitalize
enterprises through restructuring the tax system and raising
local budgets proportionately.(Uzbekistan-Budget)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LIMA -- Peruvian main mining free on board (FOB) exports
reached 2.13 billion dollars during the January-October period,
the Energy and Mines Ministry said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Gold,the most outstanding Peruvian mining export which ranks
the first place together with copper, increased by 55.6 percent
the total value of its sales abroad.
</P>
<P>
Peru sold a total of 641.6 million dollars of gold during the
first 10 months of the year,compared with 412.2 million dollars
in the same period of 1997.(Peru-mining)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PANAMA CITY -- Panama's exports to other Central American
countries are expected to increase next year following the
signing of a series of free trade agreements, authorities said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that Panama's exports to the Central
American region exceeded 40.5 million U.S. dollars in the first
10 months this year and are expected to surpass 50 million
dollars at the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
Panamanian Foreign Trade Ministry spokesman Felipe Balelo
said bilateral free trade agreements allow the elimination of
customs tariffs on certain products, and in turn would help boost
the country's export revenues.(Panama-Central America-Trade)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PANAMA CITY -- Panama would restart tuna fishing in the
Pacific Ocean next February following the United States' lift of
its embargo on tuna fishing and marketing, an official said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The move, said Marine Resources Administration director
Arnulfo Franco, would help Panama recover losses amounting to 150
billion U.S. dollars a year.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. tuna embargo was initially applied to Mexico in 1991
and later extended to Southern Pacific nations in response to
environmentalists' allegation that tuna capture kills dolphins as
the imperiled species often get snared in tuna nets.(Panama-Tuna
Fishing) 
</P>
