<DOCNO> XIE19981226.0091 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Textile Industry Declining </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 26 (Xinhua) -- China manufactured less
textile products in the first ten months this year, according to
the latest figures released by the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The output of yarn dropped by 1.8 percent to 4.18 million tons
from the same period last year, and that of cloth fell by 5.3
percent to 14 billion meters.
</P>
<P>
The output of cotton and chemical fiber blend dropped by 8.2
percent to 4.8 billion meters while that of pure chemical fiber
increased by 9 percent to 2.55 billion meters.
</P>
<P>
The January-October period also saw a decline in the production
of knitting wool and woolen piece goods. The output of knitting
wool decreased by 9.1 percent to 253,700 tons and that of woolen
piece goods dropped by 12.2 percent to 210 million meters.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the output of silk fell by 13.2 percent to
49,800 tons.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has been restructuring the textile
industry since early this year, cutting outmoded spindles for both
cotton and wool spinning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
