in the 115-strong fleet, collided with Bright Morning Star. The
83-foot maxi ketch did not appear to have the right of way.
</P>
<P>
Early placings followed the favored list with Australian maxi
Wild Thing third out of the heads.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of onlookers gathered to see the entrants embark
upon their 630-nautical mile sail south and across to Hobart on
the island state of Tasmania. 
