<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Diarrhea Spreading Fast in Northern Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, December 26 (Xinhua) -- Diarrhea has broken out in
Bangladesh's six northern districts and at least 35 people have
already died of the disease, said news reports reaching here
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The diarrhea-attacked districts are Jaipurhat, Bogra, Kurigram,
Hatibandha, Rangpur and Lalmonirhat. Patients, most of them
children, are being admitted to hospitals everyday.
</P>
<P>
"Rotavirus" germs spread very quickly in severe winter causing
diarrhea, a doctor of Civil Surgeon Office confirmed.
</P>
<P>
At least 1,493 people were attacked with diarrhea in a
fortnight from December 11, according to the reports.
</P>
<P>
At present, district and sub-district hospitals have no
sufficient saline to distribute among the affected people, and the
price of saline has gone up substantially.
</P>
<P>
In Bogra district, two people died of diarrhea and over 2,000
have been affected.
</P>
<P>
Consumption of adulterated foodstuffs, and lack of pure
drinking water and medicare facilities were blamed for the
outbreak of the disease.
</P>
<P>
Medical teams are now working in the diarrhea affected areas to
prevent the disease from further spreading. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
