<HEADLINE> Yugoslav Troops Successfully Defend Borders, Defense Council </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, December 25 (Xinhua) -- The Yugoslav State Council
on Friday praised Yugoslav troops for doing an excellent job in
defending the country's border with neighboring Albania.
</P>
<P>
The acknowledgment came in a report issued by the presidential
military office and carried by the Tanjug news agency after a
council meeting presided over by Yugoslav President Slobodan
Milosevic.
</P>
<P>
The council said it hoped the fiscal 1999 budget can
prioritize the army's combat readiness and army commanders'
living conditions.
</P>
<P>
The Yugoslav State Defense Council consists of presidents of
the Yugoslav Federation, the Republic of Serbia and Republic of
Montenegro as well as other senior leaders.
</P>
<P>
Milosevic, Serbian President Milan Milutinovic and Montenegrin
President Milo Djukanovic attended the council meeting on
Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
