<HEADLINE> Fresh Fighting Reported in Kosovo, Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Fresh fighting broke out in
Kosovo, of Yugoslavia, in the past week, with casualties on both
the government side and the armed ethnic Albanians, official
Tanjug news agency reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
A military source was quoted saying that a group of ethnic
Albanians used rifles, hand grenades and mortars to ambush an
army convoy on the highway between Pristina, capital of Kosovo,
and the northern city of Podujevo, on Thursday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Several ethnic Albanians were killed and two government
soldiers wounded in the crossfire.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, Serb police forces shot dead several armed
ethnic Albanians in Podujevo while they were hunting down killers
of a Serb policeman who died on Monday, the report said
</P>
<P>
William Walker, chief of the peace verification mission of the
Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE) in
Kosovo, expressed deep concern over the ongoing bloodshed in the
region and urged both sides to exercise maximum restraint.
</P>
</TEXT>
