<HEADLINE> Prices of Raw Materials in China Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 26 (Xinhua) -- The latest figures from the
National Bureau of Statistics show that China's raw materials
prices dropped in the third quarter this year.
</P>
<P>
The price index of total raw materials in September was 94.11,
taking that of the same period last year as 100. The price index
stood at 94.03 in July and 92.88 in August.
</P>
<P>
The price index of non-ferrous metal materials and electric
wire stood at 86 in September, representing the biggest decrease
in price.
</P>
<P>
The price of timber and paper pulp remained comparatively
stable in September with a price index of 97.09, the highest of
all.
</P>
<P>
Experts have predicted that the prices of raw materials are
expected to rebound gradually now that the government has taken
measures to substantially increase investment in infrastructure
construction.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
