<HEADLINE> Australia to Probe Tennis Abuse Claims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 26 (Xinhua) -- The Australian government
will investigate claims that female tennis players had been
subjected to starvation diets and verbal abuse at the Australian
Institute of Sport (AIS), according to reports from Sydney.
</P>
<P>
The reports Saturday said that at least 34 women awarded
scholarships at the AIS tennis program said the training regime
destroyed their careers.
</P>
<P>
Players interviewed were involved from the program's inception
in 1981 until 1995. Some players said they were under such
pressure to lose weight they developed eating disorders.
</P>
<P>
Australia has several ace men's players including Patrick
Rafter and Mark Philippoussis.
</P>
<P>
But the women's players have failed to reach the standard of
the men over the past decade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
