<HEADLINE> China's Output of Spirit Falls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 26 (Xinhua) -- The output of spirit in China
tumbled in the first ten months this year, according to the
National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
China produced 3.98 million tons of spirit between January and
October, down by seven percent against the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The output of beer grew by 7.2 percent to 17.8 million tons in
the January-October period, and that of soft drink hit eight
million tons, up by 19.4 percent over the same 1997 period.
</P>
<P>
Surveys have showed that more Chinese, who used to drink liquor
only, are changing their drinking habits. 
