<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, December 25 (Xinhua) -- There are 1.8 scientists or
engineers for every 1,000 people in Cuba, more than the average
of the underdeveloped world and some members of the developed
world.
</P>
<P>
According to a study published here Friday, more than 34,200
Cubans now work in science and technology units. Of the total,
30 percent are university graduates and 42 percent are medium
level technicians.
</P>
<P>
And as 21,600 professors are working at the country's
universities, many of them are involved in research and
development projects sponsored by the Ministry of Higher
Education, mostly on applicable technologies.
</P>
<P>
In addition, researchers also work with institutions of the
central government to extend the application of technologies.
