<HEADLINE> Honduras: Christmas Toll Down 40% From Last Year's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEGUCIGALPA, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Forty-three Hondurans
died and 44 others were injured in accidents or violent incidents
during Christmas celebrations this year, down 40 percent from
last year, police sources said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Some 20 children were taken to hospitals with burns of
different degrees of intensity caused by fireworks, prodding
police to probe into the sale of high-power fireworks already
forbidden by the authorities.
</P>
<P>
The deaths registered this Christmas included 36 homicides,
two in traffic accidents, said National Police spokesman Hector
Mejia, adding that most accidents or incidents were in the
country's north.
</P>
<P>
There were 36 road accidents during the season.
</P>
<P>
During last year's festivities, 73 people died and 77 others
suffered injuries. The spokesman attributed the lower casualties
to the information campaigns carried out by the authorities.
</P>
