<HEADLINE> Food Hygiene Improved in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 26 (Xinhua) -- More food products in the
market have met State requirements on food hygiene, reported
today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Health yesterday released the results of a
nationwide inspection on food hygiene, says an article carried by
the paper, and according to the report, 83.9 percent of the food
in China is up to national standards.
</P>
<P>
