enforcement and the gradually improving market economy. However,
problems still exit and call for strengthened inspections to
provide higher-quality and safer food for the public.
</P>
<P>
The article listed the problems such as microbe contamination,
inadequate knowledge of nutrition, excessive use of chemical
additives, and content of harmful heavy metals such as lead.
