<HEADLINE> McGwire Voted AP Top Sports Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 25 (Xinhua) -- McGwire, who broke Roger
Maris' record and set a new mark by hitting 70 baseball homers,
was the overwhelming winner for the Associated Press Sports Story
of the Year.
</P>
<P>
The St. Louis Cardinals first baseman received 1,433 points in
the annual balloting, AP reported today.
</P>
<P>
John Elway and the Denver Broncos, who won their first Super
Bowl, were second with 972 points.
</P>
<P>
The New York Yankees were third with 789 points for winning a
record 125 games in the regular and postseason, the NBA lockout
was fourth with 688 points, and Michael Jordan leading the
Chicago Bulls to their third straight title was fifth with 468.
</P>
</TEXT>
