<HEADLINE> Cruzeiro Has Final Chance to Win Soccer Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, December 25 (Xinhua) -- Cruzeiro has a third
and final chance to wrest a championship title this year if they
defeat Palmeiras on Saturday in the second leg of the Mercosur
Cup soccer final.
</P>
<P>
Last week Cruzeiro lost the Brazilian Championship to the
Corinthians in a hard-fought three match series. Earlier this
year, Cruzeiro lost the Brasil Cup to its archrival Palmeiras.
</P>
<P>
Based in Belo Horizonte, Cruzeiro won from Palmeiras 2-1 in
the first leg of the Mercosur Cup finals on December 16. Cruzeiro
needs only a tie to capture the title, while Palmeiras needs to
win by at least two goals in Sao Paulo. If Palmeiras wins by less
than two goals, a third and final game will be played on December
29. 
</P>
</TEXT>
