<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment For Industry In Eastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, December 26 (Xinhua) -- China's coastal city of
Qingdao had 1.5 times more overseas investment in its industrial
and communications sectors in the first three quarters of the year
than for the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
According to Sun Jiashun, director of the city's Economic
Commission, there was 223.4 million U.S. dollars worth of overseas
investment in 120 new projects approved by the city government in
the first three quarters.
</P>
<P>
The projects have a combined investment of 460.7 million
U.S. dollars, 1.9 times the amount for the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
Overseas-funded companies make up the majority of companies in
Qingdao's industrial and communications sectors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
